The paper deals with the problem of privacy in cloud-based machine learning, specifically in the context of secure neural network inference. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on privacy and security, cs.CR is the most likely category. The other categories are also possible because the paper deals with the implementation of efficient protocols and optimization techniques for neural network inference.
